# 🚀 Day 02 - CRM Foundation with HubSpot

## Objective

The objective of Day 2 was to understand why a Customer Relationship Management (CRM) platform is the foundation of every Go-To-Market (GTM) system and how it acts as the single source of truth for customer and revenue data.

Rather than simply learning how to use HubSpot, the focus was on understanding how a GTM Engineer models business data, customizes CRM objects, and prepares the CRM for automation.

---

# Learning Outcomes

During today's learning, I explored the core architecture of HubSpot CRM and understood how different business entities are represented.

## CRM Objects

### Contact

Represents an individual person interacting with the business.

Example Properties:
- Full Name
- Work Email
- Phone Number
- Job Title

---

### Company

Represents the organization associated with one or more contacts.

Example Properties:
- Company Name
- Industry
- Employee Count
- Annual Revenue
- Website

---

### Deal

Represents a potential sales opportunity.

Example Properties:
- Deal Name
- Pipeline Stage
- Deal Value
- Expected Close Date
- Deal Owner

---

# Sales Pipeline

A custom sales pipeline was designed to represent the customer journey from first interaction to conversion.

```
New Lead
    ↓
Qualified
    ↓
Demo Scheduled
    ↓
Proposal Sent
    ↓
Negotiation
    ↓
Closed Won
    ↓
Closed Lost
```

This pipeline helps Sales teams understand where every opportunity is in the buying journey and improves revenue forecasting.

